[3] USA (Washington state, Clark county)
Date: Fri 8 Feb 2019 10:22 AM
Source: USA Today [abridged, edited]
https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/health/2019/01/30/measles-outbreak-washington-anti-vaccine-what-know/2719315002/


A measles outbreak is rapidly spreading across a Washington county known for choosing not to vaccinate its children, and health officials have declared a public health emergency.

As of [Thu 7 Feb 2019], Clark county, Washington, which is about 9 miles [about 14.5 km] away from Portland, Oregon, identified 49 confirmed cases [currently 55 -- see above] and 11 suspected cases since the beginning of the year [2019]. Most cases are affecting children younger than 10.

The county has one of the lowest vaccination rates in the state: more than 22 percent of public school students did not complete their vaccinations, The Oregonian reported, citing state records.

[Byline: Ashley May]

